00:03:35.380 --> 00:03:37.505
Now, this video is about
to take a sharp right turn

00:03:37.505 --> 00:03:38.750
into historical storytelling.

00:03:38.750 --> 00:03:40.930
So hold onto your pipettes
and your ear buds.

00:03:40.930 --> 00:03:42.580
Now anhydrobiosis
is not something

00:03:42.580 --> 00:03:44.230
that we have
recently discovered.

00:03:44.230 --> 00:03:46.000
In fact, it's first
recorded observation

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:49.245
was in 1702 by Anton
van Leeuwenhoek.

00:03:49.245 --> 00:03:50.620
Now, if his name
sounds familiar,

00:03:50.620 --> 00:03:52.287
that's because he's
often referred to as

00:03:52.287 --> 00:03:53.860
the father of microbiology.

00:03:53.860 --> 00:03:56.350
And he made great strides
in improving the microscope

00:03:56.350 --> 00:03:57.940
and was the first
person to describe

00:03:57.940 --> 00:03:59.320
single-celled organisms.

00:03:59.320 --> 00:04:01.355
Now, he called these
little guys animalcules.

00:04:01.355 --> 00:04:02.980
And at the age of
70, he wrote a letter

00:04:02.980 --> 00:04:06.700
to the Royal Society entitled,
"On Certain Animalcules Found

00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:08.927
in the Sediments in Gutters
of the Roofs of Houses."

00:04:08.927 --> 00:04:11.260
Now, I'm actually going to
read you a little bit of what

00:04:11.260 --> 00:04:13.660
he wrote because I
feel like paraphrasing

00:04:13.660 --> 00:04:15.280
Leeuwenhoek would be a crime.

00:04:15.280 --> 00:04:17.170
"I have often placed
the animalcules

00:04:17.170 --> 00:04:20.140
I have before described
out of the water,

00:04:20.140 --> 00:04:23.320
not leaving the quantity of
a grain of sand adjoining

00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:25.660
to them, in order
to see whether, when

00:04:25.660 --> 00:04:28.030
all the water about
them was evaporated

00:04:28.030 --> 00:04:31.270
and they were exposed to air,
their bodies would burst,

00:04:31.270 --> 00:04:34.120
as I had often seen
in other animalcules.

00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:37.780
But now I found that when almost
all the water was evaporated

00:04:37.780 --> 00:04:40.540
so that the creature could no
longer be covered with water,

00:04:40.540 --> 00:04:42.760
nor move itself
as usual, it then

00:04:42.760 --> 00:04:45.890
contracted itself
into an oval figure

00:04:45.890 --> 00:04:47.500
and in that state remained.

00:04:47.500 --> 00:04:50.080
Nor could I perceive that
the moisture evaporated

00:04:50.080 --> 00:04:53.230
from its body, for it
preserved its oval and round

00:04:53.230 --> 00:04:54.970
shape unhurt.

00:04:54.970 --> 00:04:57.820
In order to more fully satisfy
myself in this respect,

00:04:57.820 --> 00:05:00.790
on the 3rd of September,
about 7 in the morning,

00:05:00.790 --> 00:05:03.730
I took some of this dry
sediment, which I had taken out

00:05:03.730 --> 00:05:05.890
of the leaden gutter
and had stood almost two

00:05:05.890 --> 00:05:08.290
days in my study and
put a little of it

00:05:08.290 --> 00:05:11.170
into two separate
glass tubes, wherein

00:05:11.170 --> 00:05:13.960
I poured some rainwater which
had been boiled and afterwards

00:05:13.960 --> 00:05:15.070
cooled.

00:05:15.070 --> 00:05:16.690
As soon as I poured
on the water,

00:05:16.690 --> 00:05:19.660
I stirred the whole about
that the sediment which,

00:05:19.660 --> 00:05:21.670
by means of the
hairs in it seemed

00:05:21.670 --> 00:05:24.610
to adhere like a solid
body, might the sooner

00:05:24.610 --> 00:05:26.200
be mixed with the water.

00:05:26.200 --> 00:05:28.390
And when it had settled to
the bottom of the glass,

00:05:28.390 --> 00:05:31.810
I examined it and perceived
some of the animalcules lying

00:05:31.810 --> 00:05:33.730
closely heaped together.

00:05:33.730 --> 00:05:36.910
In a short time afterwards, they
began to extend their bodies.

00:05:36.910 --> 00:05:38.890
And in half an hour, at
least a hundred of them

00:05:38.890 --> 00:05:40.925
were swimming about the
glass, though the whole

00:05:40.925 --> 00:05:42.550
of the sediment which
I had put into it

00:05:42.550 --> 00:05:46.990
did not, in my judgment, exceed
the weight of two grains.

00:05:46.990 --> 00:05:48.880
The preceding kinds
of experiment I

00:05:48.880 --> 00:05:51.945
had many times repeated
with the same success.

00:05:51.945 --> 00:05:54.070
And in particular, with
some of this sediment which

00:05:54.070 --> 00:05:56.920
had been kept in my
study about five months,

00:05:56.920 --> 00:05:58.960
and upon pouring on
it rainwater which

00:05:58.960 --> 00:06:02.290
had been boiled and afterwards
cooled, I saw in a few hours

00:06:02.290 --> 00:06:05.800
time many of the animalcules
before described.

00:06:05.800 --> 00:06:10.330
And if, after being so long in
a dry state, these animalcules

00:06:10.330 --> 00:06:13.480
upon water being given to
them can unfold their bodies

00:06:13.480 --> 00:06:15.800
and move about in
the usual manner,

00:06:15.800 --> 00:06:19.000
we may conclude that
in many places, where

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:22.870
in summertime the waters
stagnate and at length dry up,

00:06:22.870 --> 00:06:25.930
there may be many kinds
of animalcules which,

00:06:25.930 --> 00:06:28.180
though not originally
in those waters,

00:06:28.180 --> 00:06:32.320
may be carried thither by
waterfowl in the water or mud

00:06:32.320 --> 00:06:35.080
adhering to their
feet or feathers."

00:06:35.080 --> 00:06:38.590
Now, that letter is
over 300 years old.

00:06:38.590 --> 00:06:42.040
And that moment of
observed discovery

00:06:42.040 --> 00:06:44.050
is still so cool to me today.

00:06:44.050 --> 00:06:46.420
And it's so cool
that we can read that

00:06:46.420 --> 00:06:49.180
and read his original
words and experience

00:06:49.180 --> 00:06:50.590
that excitement with him.

00:06:50.590 --> 00:06:53.110
Now, it's most likely that the
animals that Leeuwenhoek saw

00:06:53.110 --> 00:06:54.250
were rotifers.

00:06:54.250 --> 00:06:57.790
But it is also possible that
his samples contained protozoa,

00:06:57.790 --> 00:07:00.870
nematodes, and tardigrades.

